Hemp plants are very commonly known for producing CBD; however, it truly has many more different uses! Every single part of the hemp plant can be repurposed into something else. None of it has to go to waste.

The stalk can be turned into paper, rope, insulation, animal bedding, or textiles. The seeds can be used as a dietary supplement, fuel, granola, or beer. The roots are great for compost and mulch. The leaves can be used to make CBD!

Many things that you already use every day can be made from hemp. It is a very versatile plant, and it is also a very low maintenance plant to grow.
